<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="HB0418" sponsor="Jordan D. Teuscher" designation="HB" otherSponsor="" otherHouse="Senate" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL1371" date="1/28/2026 13:01:153" printDate="01-28 13:33" subVer="0" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>4</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="07/01/2026"><seclist><sect action="E" src="code" buid="1" uid="C53G-6-S408_2026070120260701" sort="53G06 04080020260701" mtype="section" effdate="07/01/2026">53G-6-408</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="3" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="05/06/2026"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">School Class Size Requirements</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Jordan D. Teuscher</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>Senate Sponsor: </otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><gdhead lineno="4">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5">This bill establishes a class size limitation within the public education system.</gd><hphead lineno="6">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="7" slineno="0-7">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8" level="1">defines terms;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9" level="1">establishes a class size limitation;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10" level="1">allows for a certain variance from the class size limitation; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11" level="1">provides certain rulemaking authority to the State Board of Education.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="13">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14">Other Special Clauses:<ocl type="effdate" sort="2" numlevel="1" lineno="15" slineno="0-15">This bill provides a special effective date.</ocl></oc><sa numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saent numlevel="1" lineno="17" slineno="0-17"><snhead>ENACTS:</snhead><sn num="53G-6-408" src="code" uid="C53G-6-S408_2026070120260701" buid="1" sort="53G06 04080020260701" numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18"><bold>53G-6-408</bold>, Utah Code Annotated 1953</sn></saent></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="19"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="0-20">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="1" num="53G-6-408" type="enact" src="code" uid="C53G-6-S408_2026070120260701" sort="53G06 04080020260701" numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="1-2" number="53G-6-408" type="enact"><secline lineno="21">Section 1. Section <bold>53G-6-408</bold> is enacted to read:</secline><catline lineno="22"><bold>53G-6-408<parens/>. Class size limitation.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="1-14" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="1-3" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1000" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="40" groupid="28" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">As used in this section:</amend><subsection ssid="1-15" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="1-4" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2" space="false"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1001" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><subsection ssid="1-42" dnum="_-o:i-i" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3" placement="sameline"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1002" style="1" owner="i" level="1">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="132" groupid="91" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">"Class" means a course, section, or instructional period in which an LEA or <ln numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="1-5"/>school assigns a group of students to a teacher who is primarily responsible and <ln numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-6"/>accountable for the instruction of a particular subject or group of subjects during a <ln numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-7"/>specific class period or instructional block.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-43" dnum="_-o:ii-i" numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-8" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1003" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="136" groupid="94" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">"Class" does not include a large-group class.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-16" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-9" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1004" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="46" groupid="32" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">"Large-group class" means a secondary grade class:</amend><subsection ssid="1-44" dnum="_-o:i-i" numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-10" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1005" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="141" groupid="98" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">which traditionally includes a larger group of students, including a choir, band, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-11"/>orchestra, or physical education class; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-45" dnum="_-o:ii-i" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-12" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1006" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="146" groupid="102" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">for which there is adequate supervision and facilities for safe and effective <ln numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="1-13"/>instruction.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-17" dnum="_-o:c-i" numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="1-14" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1007" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(c)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="49" groupid="34" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">"Secondary grade" means grades 6 through 12 in a middle school, junior high school, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="1-15"/>and high school.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-18" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="1-16" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1" space="false"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1008" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><subsection ssid="1-64" dnum="_-o:a-i" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2" placement="sameline"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1009" style="1" owner="i" level="1">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="230" groupid="167" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">Except as provided in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53G-6-408(2)(b)">(2)(b)</xref>, an LEA or school within an LEA may <ln numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="1-17"/>not assign more than 25 students to a class.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-63" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="1-18" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1010" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="225" groupid="163" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">The limitation described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53G-6-408(2)(a)">(2)(a)</xref> does not apply:</amend><subsection ssid="1-65" dnum="_-o:i-i" numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="1-19" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1011" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="235" groupid="171" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">if the LEA or school assigns a paraeducator, paraprofessional, or teaching aide to <ln numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="1-20"/>the class the majority of classroom time; or</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-66" dnum="_-o:ii-i" numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="1-21" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1012" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="240" groupid="175" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">for an online school or course using an asynchronous learning model.</amend></subsection></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-25" dnum="_-o:3-i" numlevel="1" lineno="42" slineno="1-22" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1013" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(3)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="76" groupid="52" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">If, after the school year begins, unanticipated enrollment changes make immediate <ln numlevel="1" lineno="43" slineno="1-23"/>compliance with Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53G-6-408(2)">(2)</xref> impracticable, an LEA governing board may approve a <ln numlevel="1" lineno="44" slineno="1-24"/>temporary variance for the affected class for the remainder of the term, if the board:</amend><subsection ssid="1-27" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="45" slineno="1-25" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1014" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="79" groupid="54" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">adopts a written plan to return the class to compliance for the immediately ensuing <ln numlevel="1" lineno="46" slineno="1-26"/>term or semester; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-28" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="47" slineno="1-27" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1015" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="82" groupid="56" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">provides written notice to the parents or guardians of students in the affected class <ln numlevel="1" lineno="48" slineno="1-28"/>within 10 school days that describes the reason for the variance and the steps the <ln numlevel="1" lineno="49" slineno="1-29"/>LEA or school will take to return to compliance.</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-30" dnum="_-o:4-i" numlevel="1" lineno="50" slineno="1-30" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1" space="false"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1016" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(4)</amend></display><subsection ssid="1-61" dnum="_-o:a-i" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2" placement="sameline"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1017" style="1" owner="i" level="1">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="215" groupid="155" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">The state board shall make rules, in accordance with Title 63G, Chapter 3, Utah <ln numlevel="1" lineno="51" slineno="1-31"/>Administrative Rulemaking Act, to establish procedures for:</amend><subsection ssid="1-59" dnum="_-o:i-i" numlevel="1" lineno="52" slineno="1-32" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3" tab="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1018" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="205" groupid="148" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">LEA documentation of compliance; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-60" dnum="_-o:ii-i" numlevel="1" lineno="53" slineno="1-33" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3" tab="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1019" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="208" groupid="150" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">reporting class sizes to the state board.</amend></subsection></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-58" dnum="_-o:5-i" numlevel="1" lineno="54" slineno="1-34" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1" space="false"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1020" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(5)</amend></display><subsection ssid="1-62" dnum="_-o:a-i" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2" placement="sameline"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1021" style="1" owner="i" level="1">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="220" groupid="159" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">The state board may make rules, in accordance with Title 63G, Chapter 3, Utah <ln numlevel="1" lineno="55" slineno="1-35"/>Administrative Rulemaking Act, to:</amend><subsection ssid="1-57" dnum="_-o:i-i" numlevel="1" lineno="56" slineno="1-36" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3" tab="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1022" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(i)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="198" groupid="142" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">identify additional class types in secondary grades that:</amend><subsection ssid="1-54" dnum="_-o:A-i" numlevel="1" lineno="57" slineno="1-37" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="4"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1023" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(A)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="185" groupid="133" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">are pedagogically suited to large-group instruction; and</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-55" dnum="_-o:B-i" numlevel="1" lineno="58" slineno="1-38" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="4"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1024" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(B)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="188" groupid="135" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">for which a designation as a large-group class described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53G-6-408(5)(a)(ii)"><ln numlevel="1" lineno="59" slineno="1-39"/>(5)(a)(ii)</xref> does not impair instructional effectiveness or student safety; and</amend></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-56" dnum="_-o:ii-i" numlevel="1" lineno="60" slineno="1-40" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="3" tab="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1025" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(ii)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="191" groupid="137" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">designate a class described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53G-6-408(5)(a)(i)">(5)(a)(i)</xref> as a large-group class that is <ln numlevel="1" lineno="61" slineno="1-41"/>exempt from the limitation described in Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="53G-6-408(2)">(2)</xref>.</amend></subsection></subsection></subsection><subsection ssid="1-34" dnum="_-o:6-i" numlevel="1" lineno="62" slineno="1-42" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1026" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(6)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="106" groupid="72" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">Nothing in this section prohibits an LEA or a school within an LEA from adopting more <ln numlevel="1" lineno="63" slineno="1-43"/>stringent class size limits.</amend></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="3" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="64" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="64">Section 2.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="65"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="both">This bill takes effect on <effdate uid="code" date="7/1/2026">July 1, 2026</effdate>.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>1-28-26 1:33 PM</tm></rev></foot></leg>